<tr>
<td style="text-align:right;font-size:115%;padding-top: 0.6em;">
<div class="plainlinks hlist navbar mini">
<ul>
<li class="nv-view"><a href="/wiki/Template:Hinduism" title="Template:Hinduism"><span title="View this template">v</span></a></li>
<li class="nv-talk"><a href="/wiki/Template_talk:Hinduism" title="Template talk:Hinduism"><span title="Discuss this template">t</span></a></li>
<li class="nv-edit"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Hinduism&amp;action=edit"><span title="Edit this template">e</span></a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Sitaramdas Omkarnath</b> (17 February 1892 – 6 December 1982) was an Indian saint <sup id="cite_ref-Baul_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Baul-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Gurus_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Gurus-4"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup><sup class="reference" style="white-space:nowrap;">:115</sup><sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup> from <a href="/wiki/Bengal" title="Bengal">Bengal</a><sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6"><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup> <sup id="cite_ref-Pilgrim_7-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Pilgrim-7"><span>[</span>7<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Sri_Sri_Anandamayi_Ma.27s_Devotees_8-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Sri_Sri_Anandamayi_Ma.27s_Devotees-8"><span>[</span>8<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9"><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup> He preached the importance of chanting <a href="/wiki/N%C4%81ma" title="Nāma">Nam</a>, wrote more than 150 books to promote the essence of Indian scriptures, built more than 60 temples and ashrams all across India, and founded the spiritual organisation Akhil Bharat Jaiguru Sampradaya<sup id="cite_ref-Omkar_Math_Omkareshwar_10-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Omkar_Math_Omkareshwar-10"><span>[</span>10<span>]</span></a></sup> He started many groups, temples, mutts, both within and outside the <a href="/wiki/Sampradaya" title="Sampradaya">Sampradaya</a>—like local organisations, such as Delhi Jaiguru Sampraday, spiritual groups like Sati Sangha, Yuvak Sangha, Bidwat Sangha, Satya Dharma Prachar Sangha, etc. He was also the initiator of multiple magazines like <i>Pather Alo</i>, <i>Devjan</i>, <i>JaiGuru</i>, <i>Arya Nari</i>, <i>Paramananda</i>, and <i>Mother</i>.</p>
<p></p>
